Second Round (Sep 7 & 14)
Universidad Católica     Chi  Nacional                 Uru   1-1  0-0  1-1*
América                  Col  Universitario            Per   1-0  2-2  3-2
Oriente Petrolero        Bol  Colo Colo                Chi   2-1  0-0  2-1x
San Lorenzo              Arg  Guarani                  Bra   1-1  1-0  2-1
Bolívar                  Bol  Newell's Old Boys        Arg   1-0  0-1  1-1  2-3p
x 1st Leg Sep 8
bye: Peñarol

Quarter-Finals (Sep 21 & 28)
Newell's Old Boys        Arg  Nacional                 Uru   1-1  1-2  2-3x
San Lorenzo              Arg  Peñarol                  Uru   1-0  0-0  1-0
Oriente Petrolero        Bol  América                  Col   1-1  0-2  1-3
x 1st Leg Sep 22
  Newell's Old Boys qualify for semi-finals as best losers

Semi-Finals (Oct 5 & 12)
Nacional                 Uru  América                  Col   1-0  1-1  2-1
Newell's Old Boys        Arg  San Lorenzo              Arg   1-0  2-1  3-1

Final (Oct 19 & 26)
Newell's Old Boys        Arg  Nacional                 Uru   1-0  0-3  1-3  aet
  [Gabrich 60]
  [Vargas 13, Ostolaza 36, De Leon 78; two periods of extra time were played,
   after 90 minutes only the points from both matches (both clubs two, from
   one win each) counted, but after extra time goal difference came into play]
   
1st Leg [Rosario; att: 45,000]
[Oct 19]
Newell's Old Boys        Arg  Nacional                 Uru   1-0
  [Gabrich 60]
  [Newell's: Scopini, Llop, Theiler, Pautasso, Sensini, Marino (Fullana 81),
             Franco, Alfaro, Rossi, Batistuta, Almiron (Gabrich 46);
   Nacional: Sere, Pintos Saldanha, Revelez, De Leon, Soca, Lemos, Ostolaza,
             Cardaccio, Castro, Vargas (Carreno 89), De Lima.]

2nd Leg [Montevideo; att: 75,000]
[Oct 26]
Nacional                Uru  Newell's Old Boys          Arg   3-0    
  [Vargas 13, Ostolaza 36, De Leon 78]
  [red cards: Pautasso (Newell's) 115, Moran (Nacional) 115]
  [Nacional: Sere, Pintos Saldanha, Revelez, De Leon, Soca, Lemos, 
             Ostolaza, Cardaccio, Castro (Moran 11), Vargas (Carreno 54),
             De Lima; coach: Roberto Fleitas;
   Newell's: Scopini, Llop (Ramos), Theiler, Pautasso, Sensini, Marino, 
             Franco, Alfaro (Almiron 46), Rossi, Gabrich, Batistuta;
             coach: Jose Vudica]
 


